Thanks! I have solved this problem.

> there were a lot of errors with undefined references

You need to link the code to libonnxruntime.so, not the static libs. 
Run `./build.sh --config RelWithDebInfo --build_shared_lib --parallel` to get it.

> > there were a lot of errors with undefined references

Thanks ！I had solve this problem. But I used the command "./build.sh --config Debug --use_preinstalled_eigen --eigen_path /home/linux/eigen_lib/include/eigen3/ --use_eigenthreadpool  --build_shared_lib --update --build" to get eigen-version , it is failed. And other question is eigen library has changed in the latest version, you might need to update. For example, #include "Eigen/src/Core/arch/GPU/Half.h" , it needs to be modified to "xx/CUDA/Half.h" in cast_op,cc.

Hi,

Could you please remove the ' --use_preinstalled_eigen' flag?  onnxruntime only works with one specific eigen version, unfortunately it's not the one you're having.

commit 1456fe2fac0cd074bbbb8630ba003a7c325d015b (HEAD)
Author: Eugene Zhulenev <ezhulenev@google.com>
Date:   Tue Apr 2 15:04:26 2019 -0700

Add missing semicolon
<hr/>

BTW, you are free to use any eigen version in your source code, it won't conflict with onnxruntime's eigen. The only thing need be caution is: if you want to build onnxruntime from source code, it's better to do it in a clean docker image, and that image should only have one eigen in the whole filesystem.
Close this issue because the original problem is solved.  If you have more questions, please feel free to create a new issue.
